|trans_title=Rabbi Ovadia Yosef, shlit"a|year=2013|publisher=[[Chief Rabbinate of Israel]]|accessdate=7 October 2013}}</ref> o Setiembre 23, 1920 – Octubre 7, 2013)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.jpost.com/National-News/Shas-spiritual-leader-Rabbi-Ovadia-Yosef-dies-at-93-328072|title=Shas spiritual leader Rabbi Ovadia Yosef dies at 93|work=[[The Jerusalem Post]]|date=7 October 2013|accessdate=7 October 2013}}</ref> ing sadwang [[Pekapun a Rabbi ning Israel]] (''Chief Rabbi of Israel''),<ref>The Sephardi chief rabbi of Israel was also known as the [[Rishon LeZion (title)|Rishon leZion]]. In a broad sense, and particularly for religious purposes, Sephardi Jews are those who use a Sephardic style of liturgy. In this broader sense, the term Sephardim includes most [[Mizrahi]] Jews.</ref> metung a kikilalanan a iskolar ning [[Talmud]] ampong manimunang [[posek|autoridad]] king [[halakha|leying Hudyo]].

Migsilbi yang pekapun a ispiritual ning partido politikal a [[Shas]] king [[Knesset|Parlamentung Israeli]]. Matas ing paglalawe king kayang  halakhic a [[Responsa#In Judaism|responsa]] kareng grupung Hudyong [[Orthodox Judaism|Orthodox]], at tuturing dong maki tauling upaya (''binding'') kareng komunidad a [[Mizrahi]], a ing paglalawe kaya, a ing paglalawe kaya kanitang mabye ya, "ing pekamaulagang autoridad a halachic a mabye." ("the most important living halachic authority.)"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fr.jpost.com/servlet/Satellite?cid=1239710806422&pagename=JPost/JPArticle/ShowFull |title=Israel News &#124; Online Israeli News Covering Israel & The Jewish World – JPost |publisher=Fr.jpost.com |date= |accessdate=2012-06-06}}</ref>

